        <scopecontent>
          <p>Photographs series contains images of Woodrow and Ann Woody with friends, politicians, or other prominent persons, including Presidents Richard Nixon, George H.W. Bush, Michigan Governors George Romney, William Milliken, James Blanchard, and John Engler, Pope John Paul II, as well as automobile executives, Michigan Congressmen, and Detroit Mayor Coleman Young. The series also contains photographs of the former Hillcrest Country Club in Mount Clemens and of the Woody Pontiac dealership in Hamtramck. There are also signed portraits of various public figures.</p>
        </scopecontent>
